replies.body:
Does not make up for the loss of armor runes, hp runes, magic resist runes, and all the scaling variants. That seems to be one of the key factors in why everyone is doing so much more damage is the loss of resistances they used to get from the actual runes. These are just masteries not actual "Runes" and the small stat bonuses you gave champs does not in any way make up for the loss of that much defense.

Keeping damage relatively the same while taking away defenses does increase the damage as a whole.
{{sticker:slayer-jinx-unamused}}

The thing is, league is not a good game unless the system caters to players. There is no story aside from lore to keep you invested in a campaign. League is based on the idea that the game's concept is addicting enough to make players come back, but if we don't feel like some sort of progress is being made then it is pointless. It's like playing checkers. Fun for 2-3 games, but if you don't face a harder opponent or feel like you're "getting better" you stop. I agree with the damage, I nearly soloed a fight in bot lane at lvl 3 as taric with aftershock, however the main point is the BE system.

I sincerely love this game, I've spent close to $1,000 on it in over a year and a half. When I say i think this currency system is ridiculous and a gyp to get more money out of people, I think my complaint is valid.
{{sticker:sg-poppy}}

You Sir have summed up everything perfectly.
{{sticker:slayer-pantheon-thumbs}} 

 I think every league player should have a good read through this and give it an upvote so Riot will be forced to do something about it.
